{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\b\f0\fs20 If you want to display or work with the number of records that participate in a given Data View, you can use the \cf2 DbViewRecs() \cf1 function. \par
\par
In this example, the data is displayed by last initial. When the initial changes, the Data View is refreshed, and the number of records found is shown at the bottom of the window.\par
\par
\i\f1 Note: \i0\f0 The \cf2 EmptyDataview()\cf1  function is also useful in this regards. \cf2 EmptyDataview() \cf1 returns TRUE when \cf2 DbViewRecs()=0. \cf1\par
